<statement>
<p>
A population of bacteria is growing according to the equation <m>\displaystyle{P}{\left({t}\right)}={1950}{e}^{{{0.12}{t}}}</m>.  Estimate when the population will exceed 4410.</p>
<p>
<em>t</em>= <fillin characters="20" /> Â  </p>
<p>
Give your answer accurate to one decimal place.
</p>
</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>6.8003776406925</li></ul></p><p><m>\displaystyle{P}{\left({t}\right)}={1950}{e}^{{{0.12}{t}}}</m></p>
<p>
<m>\displaystyle{4410}={1950}{e}^{{{0.12}{t}}}</m></p>
<p>
<m>\displaystyle\frac{{4410}}{{1950}}={e}^{{{0.12}{t}}}</m></p>
<p>
<m>\displaystyle{\ln{{\left(\frac{{4410}}{{1950}}\right)}}}={0.12}{t}</m></p>
<p>
<m>\displaystyle\frac{{\ln{{\left(\frac{{4410}}{{1950}}\right)}}}}{{0.12}}={t}</m></p>
<p>
<m>\displaystyle{t}={6.8003776406925}</m></p>
</solution>
